title: Show HN: Twofer Goofer, Wordle-inspired rhyme game built with Stable Diffusion
text: Loved the daily shareable results of wordle but felt the game was a bit random. Wanted to build a version of a game I learned from my high school English teacher. Most fun part by far is using Midjourney and Stable Diffusion to make each day’s art!

Show HN: An interactive data viz cookbook built with PyScript and Pyodide
text:
Hi everyone,

I've been working with PyScript these past days. I believe it has the potential to be a very powerful learning tool, so I've been working on creating interactive cookbooks/cheat sheets that people can use as a reference when learning how to use popular Python libraries.

You can get the code or contribute here: https://github.com/dylanjcastillo/python-dataviz-cookbook/

Or check another interactive cheat sheet I made: https://pandas.dylancastillo.co/
